40|$|Announcements of {{syndication}} loans increase borrowers' shareholder wealth if {{they are}} <b>revolving</b> <b>credit</b> agreements but not {{if they are}} term loans. Share price responses to <b>revolving</b> <b>credit</b> announcements are positive and significant, whereas the wealth effect for term loans is negative and significant. The results show that announcements from both the financial press and commercial information providers can affect borrower share price reaction. Overall, single syndication announcements {{appear to be more}} newsworthy than multiple announcements reported in the financial press, and we find evidence of information leakage, post-announcement drift, or both. 2004 The Southern Finance Association and the Southwestern Finance Association. ...|$|R
