50|$|In Europe, {{over the}} past few years, other {{vehicles}} such as <b>credit</b> <b>funds</b> have begun to appear on the market. <b>Credit</b> <b>funds</b> are open-ended pools of debt investments. Unlike CLOs, however, they are not subject to ratings oversight or restrictions regarding industry or ratings diversification. They are generally lightly levered (two or three times), allow managers significant freedom in picking and choosing investments, and are subject to being marked to market.|$|R
